  "decision_conditions": [
    "The submitted information proposes photovoltaic panels to be installed on a roof within one metre of the external edge of that roof. The proposal, therefore, fails to comply with provision J.1(c), Class J, Part 14, Schedule 2 of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015 (as amended).",
    "The application submission has not demonstrated that the photovoltaic panels would, so far as practicable, be sited so as to minimise its effect on the external appearance of the building and be sited so as to minimise its impact on the amenity of the area. Consequently, the proposal would not comply with Condition J.4(1)(a), Class J, Part 14, Schedule 2 of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015 (as amended).",
    "Insufficient information has been submitted to demonstrate that the glare impact from the photovoltaic panels would not cause unacceptable harm to occupants of neighbouring land. The proposal, therefore, fails to comply with Condition J.4(2), Class J, Part 14, Schedule 2 of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015 (as amended)."
